    <fr:title text="Distributed Shared Memory (GPU)">Distributed Shared Memory (GPU)</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Because the <fr:link href="/W2D5/" title="Cooperative Thread Array (CTA)" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/W2D5/" display-uri="W2D5" type="local">CTAs</fr:link> in a cluster live on neighboring <fr:link href="/OGCS6/" title="Streaming Multiprocessor (SM)" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/OGCS6/" display-uri="OGCS6" type="local">SMs</fr:link> connected by a dedicated SM-to-SM network, the shared memory of all CTAs in the cluster is exposed as a single logical address space. A thread in one CTA can read/write/atomic into another CTA's shared memory directly, without round-tripping through global memory (L2/DRAM).</html:p>
    <html:div class="code-figure">
      <html:div class="code-filename">cooperative_group.cu</html:div>
      <html:pre>
        <html:code class="language-cpp"><![CDATA[#include <cooperative_groups.h>
namespace cg = cooperative_groups;

__global__ void __cluster_dims__(2,1,1) kernel(...) {
    cg::cluster_group cluster = cg::this_cluster();
    extern __shared__ int smem[];

    // Get a pointer to another CTA's shared memory
    unsigned int rank = cluster.block_rank();      // my CTA's id in cluster
    int *remote = cluster.map_shared_rank(smem, /*target rank=*/ rank ^ 1);

    // Now read/write the neighbor's shared memory
    remote[threadIdx.x] = threadIdx.x;

    cluster.sync();   // cluster-wide barrier
}]]></html:code>
      </html:pre>
    </html:div>
  </fr:mainmatter>
