            <fr:title text="Graphics Processing Cluster (GPC)">Graphics Processing Cluster (GPC)</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A Graphics Processing Cluster (GPC) is a top-level hardware partition inside an NVIDIA GPU. It's one level up from the <fr:link href="/OGCS6/" title="Streaming Multiprocessor (SM)" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/OGCS6/" display-uri="OGCS6" type="local">SM</fr:link> in the chip's hierarchy.</html:p>
            <html:p>As of Hopper, <fr:link href="/OGCS6/" title="Streaming Multiprocessor (SM)" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/OGCS6/" display-uri="OGCS6" type="local">SMs</fr:link> located in the same GPC are connected via an SM-to-SM network, enabling <fr:link href="/OGCS8/" title="Distributed Shared Memory (GPU)" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/OGCS8/" display-uri="OGCS8" type="local">DSMEM</fr:link>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
